Anheuser-Busch InBev, Aviva, Ferrovial: European Equity Preview

-- B y   J e f f   K e a r n s
-- 
2011-04-12T04:00:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/anheuser-busch-inbev-aviva-ferrovial-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in European trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The Stoxx Europe 600 Index fell 0.2 percent to 280.99. The
Stoxx 50 Index slipped 0.1 percent to 2645.69. The Euro Stoxx 50
Index, a benchmark for nations using the euro, declined 0.3
percent to 2,974.58.  Allied Irish Banks Plc (ALBK)  : The Dublin-based,
government-controlled lender is scheduled to report full-year
net income. The shares dropped 11 percent to 0.25 euros.  Anheuser-Busch InBev NV (ABI)  : AB InBev Zone President
Luiz Fernando Edmond, who heads the world’s largest brewer’s
operations in  North America , sold 43,000 of the beermaker’s
shares for an average of 40.87 euros apiece in trades on
Euronext Brussels, according to a regulatory filing. AB InBev
advanced 0.8 percent to 41.27 euros.  Aviva Plc (AV/ LN): Britain’s second-biggest insurer by
market value plans to sell a 478 million-euro ($690 million)
stake in  Delta Lloyd NV (DL) , the Dutch insurer it took public in
2009. The stock advanced 0.1 percent to 452.7 pence.  Banco Espanol de Credito SA (BTO)  : The unit of Banco
Santander SA (SAN SM) is scheduled to publish its first-quarter
earnings before trading starts. Banesto shares declined 0.2
percent to 6.68 euros.  Delta Lloyd  NV (DL NA): Aviva Plc said it plans to sell
about 25 million shares of the Dutch insurer in a private
placement that’s being managed by Morgan Stanley and Goldman
Sachs Group Inc. as Britain’s second-biggest insurer cedes
majority control of company it took public in 2009. Delta Lloyd
dropped 1.9 percent to 18.99 euros.  Ferrovial SA (FER)  :  Spain ’s second-largest builder by
market capitalization plans to borrow about $2.5 billion in
euros and pounds to refinance debt, according to three people
with knowledge of the situation. The stock retreated 1.3 percent
to 9.17 euros.  Pearson Plc (PSON)  : The education and media publishing
company which owns the Financial Times newspaper has extended
the offer period for Education Development International Plc
(EDD LN) to April 26 after having received acceptances
representing about 70.7 percent of the issued shared capital of
EDI, Pearson said in an e-mailed statement. The shares were
unchanged at 1,104 pence.  Retail Estates NV (RET)  :  Belgium ’s biggest owner of out-
of-town stores agreed to buy commercial properties generating
annual rental income of 275,000 euros ($397,000) from KBC Group
NV’s insurance unit Fidea NV for 4.29 million euros in stock.
Retail Estates declined 0.5 percent to 48.37 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jeff Kearns in  New York  at 
